 lawsuit against the parties by Jennifer Neill, who under the on-air name “Jen Posner”, was an employee of TTWN Media as a traffic reporter from 2000 to 2017. She started reporting traffic for DeBella’s show when he joined WMGK in 2002 and was promoted to co-host in 2010 where her TTWN employment was subcontracted to then WMGK owner [[Greater Media]]. According to the lawsuit, Neill claimed that DeBella forced himself on her at work repeatedly, made unwanted advances, and asked for sexual favors, while station management did nothing. She later filed a complaint with the Pennsylvania Human Relations Commission in September 2016 after which she was asked to return to work or take a leave of absence while an independent investigation was conducted (Neill did return for one show and left), but six weeks later after the investigation was completed she was never told of the details and was given the opportunity to return or resign, the latter of which she did in January 2017 after she was demoted to traffic reporter at TTWN. The lawsuit resulted in a settlement between the principal parties on July 13.<ref>[https://radioinsight.com/headlines/135363/wmgk-morning-host-john-debella-beasley-media-iheartmedia-sued-sexual-harrassment/ “John DeBella Reaches Settlement In Sexual Harassment Case”] from Radio Insight (July 18, 2018)</ref><ref>[https://www.courierpostonline.com/story/news/local/south-jersey/2018/07/18/neill-debella-wmgk-harassment-lawsuit-settled/796148002/ “Former sidekick settles suit against radio host John DeBella”] from The Courier-Post ([[Cherry Hill, New Jersey]]) (July 13, 2018)</ref> |- |[[CKTO-FM]] [[Truro, Nova Scotia|Truro]], [[Nova Scotia, Canada|Nova Scotia]] flips from Hot AC/classic rock to active rock.{{citation needed|date=March 2018}} |- |style="text-align:center;"|'''24''' |After a five-year run with All-80s Music, [[WMGA]] [[Kenova, West Virginia|Kenova]]/[[Huntington, West Virginia]] flips to AC, marking a return to the format, as it previously