ased]] by [[Gannett Company|Gannett]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/milwaukee/news/2018/07/27/milwaukee-espn-radio-owner-buys-radio-stations.html|title=Milwaukee ESPN Radio owner buys radio stations WTMJ-AM, WKTI-FM|last=Kirchen|first=Rich|date=27 July 2018|work=[[American City Business Journals|Milwaukee Business Journal]]|accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref> |- |style="text-align:center;"|'''28''' |Just one year after launching with a Rhythmic Hot AC direction, only to later segue to Top 40/CHR, [[KQFX-FM]] [[Amarillo, Texas|Amarillo]] surprisingly flipped formats to Regional Mexican, simulcasting [[KBEX (FM)|KBCX]] [[Dalhart, Texas|Dalhart]]. The flip occurred during a [[Salvation Army]] sock drive remote the staffers were doing and, they were notified of the switch during the event.<ref>[https://radioinsight.com/headlines/169727/viva-media-flips-wild-104-3-amarillo-in-middle-of-charity-remote/ “Viva Media Flips Wild 104.3 Amarillo In Middle Of Charity Remote”] from Radio Insight (July 31, 2018)</ref> |}
