{{World Championships in Athletics |Name =IAAF World Championships Doha 2019 |Logo = |Size = |Host city = [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] |dates= 27 September 2019 – 6 October 2019 |Optional caption = |Nations participating = |Athletes participating = |Events = |Stadium = [[Khalifa International Stadium]] |Website = {{URL|https://iaafworldathleticschamps.com/doha2019/}} |previous = [[2017 World Championships in Athletics|London 2017]] |next = [[2021 World Championships in Athletics|Eugene 2021]] }}
The seventeenth edition of the '''[[IAAF]] [[World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]]''' is scheduled to be held between 27 September and 6 October 2019 in [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] at the renovated multi-purpose [[Khalifa International Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/other-sports/athletics/night-time-marathon-doha-qatar-host-4649380 |title=Night-time marathon in Doha? Qatar to host 2019 World Athletics Championships |last=Richards |first=Alex |date=18 November 2014 |website=Mirror Online |access-date=22 February 2018}}</ref>
==Host selection== Three cities applied for organising the event:<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/competitions/iaaf-world-championships/news/barcelona-doha-eugene-2019-iaaf-world-champio BARCELONA, DOHA AND EUGENE – CANDIDATE CITIES FOR 2019 IAAF WORLD CHAMPIONSHIPS]</ref> * [[Barcelona]], Spain * [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] * [[Eugene, Oregon|Eugene]] ([[Oregon]]), United States.
The final selection of the host city was carried out on November 18, 2014 in [[Monaco]].<ref name=doha>{{Citation |url=http://www.atleticalive.it/10286/iaaf-wc-2019-will-be-held-in-doha-qatar/ |title=Iaaf WC 2019 will be held in Doha, Qatar! |work=Queen Atletica}}</ref>
