The '''Sweet Harmony Traveling Revue''' was a three-week [[concert tour]] of [[country music|country]] and [[folk music|folk]] musicians [[Emmylou Harris]], [[Patty Griffin]], [[Buddy Miller]], [[Gillian Welch]], and [[David Rawlings]], which took place in August 2004.<ref name=bglobe>{{cite news|title=Harris and Co. make sweet music|url=http://articles.boston.com/2004-08-25/news/29202854_1_welch-and-rawlings-buddy-miller-songs|accessdate=5 September 2011|newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]]|date=25 August 2004}}</ref><ref name=wpost19Aug2004>{{cite news|last=McKenna|first=Dave|title=Emmylou and Friends: Somber & Sublime|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A13800-2004Aug18.html|accessdate=5 September 2011|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=19 August 2004}}</ref>   The group toured primarily in the American South, but also played in New York City (Central Park), Boston, Massachusetts (Fleet Pavilion), and Shelburne, Vermont (Shelburne Farm).

